headline: Did Buffett Sell Apple and Bank of America too Early?
summary: One of the hardest things in investing is knowing when to sell a winning stock.

headline: United Rentals (URI) Margin Miss Reinforces Investor Focus on Slower Forward Growth Expectations
summary: United Rentals (URI) delivered a net profit margin of 15.8%, down from 17.1% in the previous year. While it has posted a robust 20.3% annual EPS growth rate over the past five years, recent earnings growth turned negative for the most recent year. Looking ahead, analysts expect earnings to grow by 10.95% per year and revenue to rise 6.9% annually. Both of these paces are trailing the broader US market averages. Margins have compressed and the current share price of $914.3 sits below URI's...
